Khumar explores the complexities of love in the face of societal expectations and challenges. Faiz and Hareem, two individuals from different backgrounds, find their lives connected by destiny.Faiz, born into an affluent family, contrasts sharply with Hareem, who hails from alower-middle-class background. Despite their differences, fate weaves their paths together. Hareem, diligently working to make ends meet amid her brother Rufi's educational needs and her mother's medical expenses, faces numerous hurdles. In the midst of her struggles, Faiz, a friend of Rufi's, silently supports them financially and even gets work for Hareem, albeit discreetly.Hareem's family doesn't know that Faiz loves her, leading to a one-sided love affair. Faiz's love for Hareem remains a secret, but his mother disapproves of his association with Hareem's family due to the significant class difference. But fate decides to play its tune, and an unexpected event turns the lives of Faiz and Hareem upside down.What was this surprising turn of events that changed everything for Faiz and Hareem? Will the gap in their social status keep them apart? Can Faiz convince his mother to accept Hareem? If they marry, can they create a happy life together despite their different backgrounds and mindsets?7th Sky Entertainment Presentation Producers: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi Writer: Maha MalikDirector: Ali FaizanCast:Feroze Khan as FaizNeelam Muneer as HareemHina Bayat as Kehkasha BegumAsma Abbas as DurdanaBehroz Sabzwari as Sheikh FurqanZainab Qayoom as Dil AraaShehryar Zaidi as TaufeeqAdnan Samad as NasirSheherzade Peerzada as Hamna  Minsa Malik as Laiba Kinza Malik as AtiyaMehmood Akhtar as Zaawar  Agha Mustafa as Rayyan  Hamzah Tariq as RufiAyesha Rajpoot as ShaguftaMizna Waqas as HusnaSohail Masood as Mirza SahabBirjees Farooqui as Salma#HappilacPaints #ColorsofHappiness#Khumar#FerozeKhan#NeelamMuneer

Spread the word.Khumar Episode 46 [Eng Sub] Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints - Feroze Khan - Neelam Muneer - 20th April 2024 - Har Pal GeoKhumar Digitally Presented by Happilac PaintsKhumar is a timeless love story that delves into the challenges arising from societal class differences and the negativity that stems from them. Khumar explores the complexities of love in the face of societal expectations and challenges. Faiz and Hareem, two individuals from different backgrounds, find their lives connected by destiny.Faiz, born into an affluent family, contrasts sharply with Hareem, who hails from alower-middle-class background. Despite their differences, fate weaves their paths together. Hareem, diligently working to make ends meet amid her brother Rufi's educational needs and her mother's medical expenses, faces numerous hurdles. In the midst of her struggles, Faiz, a friend of Rufi's, silently supports them financially and even gets work for Hareem, albeit discreetly.Hareem's family doesn't know that Faiz loves her, leading to a one-sided love affair. Faiz's love for Hareem remains a secret, but his mother disapproves of his association with Hareem's family due to the significant class difference. But fate decides to play its tune, and an unexpected event turns the lives of Faiz and Hareem upside down.What was this surprising turn of events that changed everything for Faiz and Hareem? Will the gap in their social status keep them apart? Can Faiz convince his mother to accept Hareem? Spread the word.Khumar Episode 46 [Eng Sub] Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints - Feroze Khan - Neelam Muneer - 20th April 2024 - Har Pal GeoKhumar Digitally Presented by Happilac PaintsKhumar is a timeless love story that delves into the challenges arising from societal class differences and the negativity that stems from them. Khumar explores the complexities of love in the face of societal expectations and challenges. Faiz and Hareem, two individuals from different backgrounds, find their lives connected by destiny.Faiz, born into an affluent family, contrasts sharply with Hareem, who hails from alower-middle-class background. Despite their differences, fate weaves their paths together. Hareem, diligently working to make ends meet amid her brother Rufi's educational needs and her mother's medical expenses, faces numerous hurdles. In the midst of her struggles, Faiz, a friend of Rufi's, silently supports them financially and even gets work for Hareem, albeit discreetly.Hareem's family doesn't know that Faiz loves her, leading to a one-sided love affair. Faiz's love for Hareem remains a secret, but his mother disapproves of his association with Hareem's family due to the significant class difference. But fate decides to play its tune, and an unexpected event turns the lives of Faiz and Hareem upside down.What was this surprising turn of events that changed everything for Faiz and Hareem? Will the gap in their social status keep them apart? Can Faiz convince his mother to accept Hareem?
